6
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:36,400
<i>Come on. Push through.</i>

7
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:38,100
Push through. Don't give up
on me now. Come on.

8
00:00:38,100 --> 00:00:39,800
You got it. You got it.
Don't give up on me.

9
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,100
Come on ! Come on !

10
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:42,700
All right.

11
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:46,200
What's bugging you, Bobby ?

12
00:00:46,800 --> 00:00:47,900
Nothing.

13
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:55,400
You remembered ?

14
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:57,300
You're 18 today.

15
00:00:57,300 --> 00:00:58,800
You haven't talked about anything else
for three whole months.

16
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:00,000
How could I forget ?

17
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:02,800
My family did.

18
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:04,700
I'm your family now.

19
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:06,600
You know that.

20
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:07,900
Go ahead.

21
00:01:10,900 --> 00:01:13,100
It belonged to my buddy,
Johnny Hughes.

22
00:01:13,100 --> 00:01:13,900
It's a compass.

23
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:16,000
Carried it with him
on every single jump.

24
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,400
He gave that to me...

25
00:01:18,101 --> 00:01:19,301
to help me find my way.

26
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:20,900
Now it's yours.

27
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:22,500
Doesn't matter
where you been.

28
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:24,200
Only matters
where you go.

29
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,500
Listen.

30
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:30,100
I'm not talking to you
right now as your recruiter.

31
00:01:30,100 --> 00:01:31,200
Okay, I'm talking
to you as a brother,

32
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:32,900
'cause that's how I see you,
right ?

33
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:34,000
Yeah, man.

34
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,200
I am proud of you

35
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:37,300
no matter what you decide to do.

36
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,200
I want to sign my contract...

37
00:01:42,201 --> 00:01:43,201
today.

38
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:44,900
Yeah ?

39
00:01:45,100 --> 00:01:46,000
Yeah !

40
00:01:47,300 --> 00:01:49,900
Oh, you're not going to regret
this, Bobby. You're not.

41
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:51,700
The Army put me on
the right track, man.

42
00:01:51,700 --> 00:01:53,500
It's going to do
the same for you.

43
00:01:54,300 --> 00:01:55,400
Thank you.

44
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:10,900
Ah, it's so... beautiful.

45
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:33,900
<i>Homicide.</i>

46
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:34,500
Yeah.

47
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:35,800
Lil, Dad's on the line.

48
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:37,000
Mind taking a message ?

49
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,800
I'm tied up.

50
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:41,600
At ease.

51
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:48,300
Bumper, huh ?

52
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:49,800
That's what they call me.

53
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:50,900
Name's Bobby, though.

54
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:54,600
Well, Bobby, I found
Mike Donley's murder file.

55
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:56,200
Says here that he broke

56
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:58,400
into the Prestige Pawnshop
over on 6th Street.

57
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:00,800
Now, the body was found in
an alley a few hours later.

58
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,400
November 5, 2005.

59
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,900
Cops found some of the
stolen jewelry near his body.

60
00:03:04,900 --> 00:03:06,300
Figured he was jacked
for the rest.

61
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:07,800
You got some new information ?

62
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:09,600
Found the article
from the paper online.

63
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:12,300
It says the pawnshop alarm
got tripped at 11:00 p.m.

64
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,400
- So ?
- Staff Sergeant Donley

65
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:17,800
was with me at 11:00.
Putting me on a bus to Fort Bragg.

66
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,400
A ticket...

67
00:03:20,601 --> 00:03:21,701
from the night of the murder.

68
00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:24,500
- He didn't rob that store, ma'am.
- It's been four years, Bobby.

69
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:26,100
What took you so long
to come forward ?

70
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:27,600
I'm Special Forces.

71
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,200
Green Berets.

72
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:31,000
Went from training at Fort Bragg

73
00:03:31,001 --> 00:03:32,801
to two tours in Afghanistan.

74
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:34,400
Just got home.

75
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,300
Well, bus ticket doesn't
prove he was with you.

76
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:39,100
Ma'am, Army thinks one of its
top soldiers is a criminal.

77
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,600
Gotta make it right.

78
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,300
Staff Sergeant Donley
changed my life.

79
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:47,700
The least I can do is honor his.

